Eradication of Discord in Unequal Society Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- The People's Solidarity for Eradicating the Social Inequality (People's Solidarity)  called a press conference for the formation of the organization on Sept. 22 at which it urged the authorities to eliminate the discord in the unequal society, according to a news report.
 The People's Solidarity groups at least 130 civic and social bodies including the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, the Federation of Korean Trade Unions, the National Federation of Peasants Associations, the People's Solidarity of south Korea and the Citizens' Solidarity for Democratic Society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An inaugural declaration read out at the news conference put forward the tasks for social reforms in seven fields such as the guarantee of the right to the part-timers and improvement of the minimum wage system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Su Ho, chairman of the confederation, in his speech said that the part-time workers and the unemployed are the victims of the social inequality, calling on the labor movement bodies to spearhead the movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hye Gyong, representative of the Democratic Workers' Party, declared that the party would conduct activities inside the "National Assembly" for the guarantee of the rights to the workers and the improvement of the standard of their living in support of the People's Solidarity.

Information Bulletin on DPRK Issued in Switzerland 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- The Swiss Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea issued an Information Bulletin No. 9.
 The bulletin carries news that the Swiss committee presented gifts to President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation and aphorisms of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also introduces in detail the revolutionary life of the members of the family of the President on the occasion of the 50th death anniversary of Kim Po Hyon, grandfather of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Carried in the bulletin are a statement issued by the Swiss committee in denunciation of the "Ulji Focus Lens-05" joint military exercises staged by the U.S. in south Korea and articles including one condemning Japan's blasting of the "Ukishima-maru" 60 years back and its other crimes perpetrated in the past .

Japan's Disturbing Military Moves under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- Japan is contemplating setting up the command of the "rapid reaction force" of its ground "Self-Defence Force" in Jama base, Kanagawa, a U.S. forces' base in Japan, and transferring the general command of  its Air SDF to the Yokoda base of the U.S. air force in Japan under the pretext of "combating terrorism".
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun Monday observes in a signed commentary: It is Japan's plan to realize the "integration" of the SDF and the U.S. troops and coordinate the commanding system of the armed forces whereby the SDF will operate along the U.S. forces under a unified command. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hasty action taken by Japan to this end cannot be construed otherwise than a very dangerous military move, the commentary says, and continues:
 Japan can make a retrogressive revision of its present constitution anytime and a social atmosphere for it has already been created. It is against this background that Japan is frantically pushing forward the arms buildup and taking an active part in the development of the U.S. missile defence system (MD). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan regards it as the only way of its overseas aggression to tighten its military alliance with the U.S. and avail itself of the U.S. "war against terrorism".
 Precisely for this reason Japan is keen to realize the "integration" of the SDF and the U.S. troops at an early date. Through this Japan seeks to drive its SDF to overseas aggression with ease, taking advantage of the U.S. acts of aggression and war.
 It is the main strategy of Japan for overseas aggression to realize its wild ambition for staging a comeback to Korea and realize its old dream of the "Greater East Asia Co-prosperity Sphere" under the patronage of the U.S., using the Japan-U.S. military alliance as a lever for starting a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be well advised to stop acting rashly, pondering over the disastrous consequences to be entailed by its reckless moves to realize its wild ambition for overseas aggression.

Rodong Sinmun on Line of Independent Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- The idea and line of the Workers' Party of Korea on national reunification have given full play to great vitality with the support of all the fellow countrymen as they are the original and patriotic idea and line embodying national independence and the scientific and realistic idea and line serving as the most correct guidelines of the reunification movement.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The remarkable events and achievements in the north-south relations and the movement for national reunification are a clear demonstration of the validity and vitality of the Party's patriotic line of national reunification, the cornerstone of which is national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The line of national reunification the Party laid down from the outset of its foundation and has invariably maintained in the whole course of the reunification movement is the line of thorough-going national independence to achieve the complete independence and sovereignty of the country and the nation and the genuine patriotic line for the development of a reunified country and the prosperity of the whole nation.
 This line most correctly reflects the desire of all the fellow countrymen to establish the sovereignty of the nation on a nationwide scale and glorify the dignity of the nation.
 Nation-wide functions for reunification were held irrespective of differences in idea and ideology, authorities, civilians, systems and religious belief in June marking the 5th anniversary of the June 15 joint declaration and in August marking the 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation. This is a clear demonstration of the validity and vitality of the Party's line of national independence as it is an expression of the steadfast will of the fellow countrymen to establish national sovereignty.
 The 10-point programme for the great unity of the whole nation advanced by President Kim Il Sung and the five-point policy of great national unity set forth by leader Kim Jong Il in the sacred  work for national unity have served as the banner of national reconciliation and unity and the guidelines of action. The driving force of reunification has been immensely strengthened in the course of applying the 10-point programme and the five-point policy and it has become the powerful motive force of stepping up the cause of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Any ordeals and challenges cannot arrest the dynamic advance of the cause of reunification as it is guided by the just grand programme of reunification common to the nation put forward by the Party.

Russian Ensemble Performs in Wonsan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Wonsan, September 25 (KCNA) -- The visiting State Academy Ensemble of the Ministry of Interior of Russia gave its performances in Wonsan on Sept. 24 and 25.
 The ensemble's repertoire included wartime songs created and widely sung by the Soviet army and people in the crucible of the struggle against the fascist aggressors during the Great Patriotic War and colorful dances showing the national sentiment and lifestyle of the Russians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian artistes enthusiastically sang Korean songs including the immortal revolutionary paeans "Song of General Kim Il Sung" and "Song of General Kim Jong Il," deeply impressing the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They truthfully represented with high artistry wartime songs such as "Just War," "Lantern," "Polyusko-Pole," "Belachao," chorus and orchestra "The Song of Defenders of Moscow," male solo and choruses "My Heroic Soldiers," "I Have Come from Berlin," "Officers"  and "Black Crow" to the acclaim of the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dancers of the ensemble successfully depicted with refined talent and dynamic rhythms the optimistic life and emotion of the Russian soldiers and people in such numbers as "Dance of Guerrillas," "Market in Russia," "Moscow Dance Music" and "Gypsy Dance." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its presentations were well received by the audiences.

Suppression of Patriotic Youths and Students under Fire in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- Students under the general student councils of Chungang University, Dongguk University and Dankook University and members of the student committee of the Democratic Workers' Party in south Korea held a protest rally in Seoul on Sept. 21 to denounce the security authorities' crackdown on patriotic youths and students, according to a news report.
 Speakers at the rally referred to the fact that the security authorities on the same day walked away Pak Ji Hyon, director of the organizing department of the student committee of the Democratic Workers' Party who was wanted by the police, on charges of the violation of the "National Security Law." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They condemned the police for intensifying its tough counteraction for good results, charging that the police issued a summons against Chairwoman of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils Song Hyo Won and Chairman of its National Reunification Committee Kim Ji Ha on charges of spearheading the struggle for the withdrawal of the statue of MacArthur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed their will to pool the efforts of students to positively counter the security authorities' indiscriminate suppression.

Kumya Ginkgo, Natural Monument
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- There is a 2,120-odd years old ginkgo at the compound of the Anbul Temple, a historic relic, in Tonghung-ri of Kumya County, South Hamgyong Province, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The ginkgo, which has been registered as a natural monument, is 42 meters in height, 18.2 meters in the girth at the bottom and 15.5 meters in the girth at the middle.
 The tree bears more than 300 kilograms of fruits on a yearly average.
 It has two nipple-shaped knobs on its trunk. It is said that a knob comes into being once every a thousand years. The bigger one is 10 cm and the other 5 cm in diameter respectively. And they contain much starch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year the tree has produced unusually bumper fruits and dozens of sprouts shot out on its roots exposed to the ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung instructed officials to take a step to protect the tree during the Fatherland Liberation War and leader Kim Jong Il went round it during his field guidance in April Juche 92 (2003). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Kumya ginkgo is of great scientific significance.
